## Category Card Pattern

Item tiles are typically displayed inside category cards within a drag-scrollable carousel. The standard pattern is:

```
Section
├── Header row (title + "View all" link)
└── Scroll row (drag-scrollable, horizontal)
    ├── Category card (320px wide, subtle background)
    │   ├── Category header (title + "Shop all" link)
    │   └── 2×2 product grid
    │       ├── WCPItemTile
    │       ├── WCPItemTile
    │       ├── WCPItemTile
    │       └── WCPItemTile
    ├── Category card ...
    └── Category card ...
```

### Category Card Specs

| Property | Value |
|---|---|
| Width | 320px (340px at 768px+, 290px at 480px-) |
| Background | `var(--ld-semantic-color-background-subtle, #f5f5f5)` |
| Border radius | `var(--ld-primitive-scale-borderradius-100, 8px)` |
| Padding | `12px` |
| Gap (between header and grid) | `8px` |
| Grid gap | `8px` |

### Scroll Row Specs

| Property | Value |
|---|---|
| Direction | Horizontal flex |
| Gap | `12px` |
| Overflow | `overflow-x: auto` with hidden scrollbar |
| Snap | `scroll-snap-type: x mandatory` / `scroll-snap-align: start` |
| Drag scroll | Use `useDragScroll` hook for mouse drag support |

### Category Header Specs

| Element | Font size | Weight | Token |
|---|---|---|---|
| Category title | 16px | 700 | `--ld-semantic-color-text` |
| "Shop all" link | 12px | 400 | `--ld-semantic-color-link-text` (underlined) |

